WITH both teams eliminated from the Telkom Knockout competition, the focus for Mamelodi Sundowns and Kaizer Chiefs has now shifted 100% to their Absa Premiership campaign. The Brazilians are still playing catch-up in the league as a result of their participation in the Caf Champions League. They host Amakhosi in the pick of the weekend&rsquo;s Premiership matches at Loftus Versfeld on Saturday (3.30pm). The Soweto giants trail log leaders Bidvest Wits by one point after eight matches. Chiefs are third in the table with 15 points, while the Tshwane giants are second from bottom with four points from three games. Brazilians coach Pitso Mosimane, who is friends with Amakhosi coach Steve Komphela, will also renew his rivalry with his friend. The Tshwane giants wrestled the league championship title away from Amakhosi last season and also defeated them 3-1 in the Telkom Knockout final in December last year.Mosimane said their exit from the domestic cup CONTINUED ON PAGE 22